[SN]TITLE[SN]
Kevin McGuigan murder: Man charged with possessing firearm

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 53-year-old man arrested in connection with the murder of former IRA member Kevin McGuigan has been charged with possessing a firearm with intent to endanger life.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
He is due to appear before Lisburn Magistrates' Court on Thursday.
Police arrested a 26-year-old man as part of their investigation on Wednesday.
A 46-year-old man is still being questioned. Three other men and a woman have been released unconditionally.
Mr McGuigan Sr, 53, was murdered at his home at Comber Court in the Short Strand area of east Belfast last week.
Police recovered two guns in greater Belfast on Tuesday during searches connected to the investigation.
